{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019XBjbhek54o67p2Y8nkVYD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# OfficeAgent Monorepo\n     2→\n     3→AI agent platform for Office document creation (DOCX, PPTX, XLSX, PDF), running in Docker containers with Claude SDK and Azure OpenAI harnesses.\n     4→\n     5→## Shell Requirements\n     6→\n     7→**CRITICAL: Use PowerShell for all yarn, oagent, and gulp commands.** Bash/sh will fail for build/run operations. File searching (grep, find, glob) works in any shell.\n     8→\n     9→## Repository Structure\n    10→\n    11→- `agents/` - Agent implementations (create-agent, gpt-create-agent, ppt-creation-agent, ppt-edit-agent, dw-accountant-agent, dw-paralegal-agent, odsp-agent)\n    12→- `modules/` - Shared libraries (`@officeagent/*`): core, api, message-protocol, grounding, rai, excel-headless, chain-of-thought, html2pptx, json-to-docx-ooxml, mcp-proxy, gpt-agent, git-remote-spo\n    13→- `.devtools/` - CLI (`oagent`), test-client, e2e-tests, eval-browser, launcher, OCV tools\n    14→- `eval/` - Python evaluation framework (pytest-based)\n    15→- `docs/` - Architecture documentation\n    16→- `docker/` - Dockerfile, runtime package.json, docker-compose\n    17→\n    18→## Build & Run Commands\n    19→\n    20→| Command | Description |\n    21→|---------|-------------|\n    22→| `npm run setup` | First-time dev environment setup |\n    23→| `yarn build` | Build packages + Docker image (Docker Desktop must be running) |\n    24→| `yarn start` | Start Docker container + test client |\n    25→| `yarn start:compose` | Start via docker-compose (supports scaling) |\n    26→| `yarn stop` | Stop Docker container |\n    27→| `yarn reload` | Hot-reload code into running container |\n    28→| `yarn test` | Run all tests (Jest + pytest) |\n    29→| `yarn lint` | ESLint across all workspaces |\n    30→\n    31→## Package Management\n    32→\n    33→- **Buildtime**: Yarn 4.10.3 workspaces with `lage` task runner\n    34→- **Runtime (in container)**: npm for Node packages (`docker/package.json`), pip/tdnf for Python (`docker/Dockerfile`)\n    35→- Packages use `@officeagent/` scope with `workspace:^` linking\n    36→\n    37→## Testing\n    38→\n    39→- **TypeScript/JS**: Jest with ts-jest preset. Tests in `**/tests/**/*.test.ts`\n    40→- **Python**: pytest with coverage. Tests in `tests/test_*.py`. See `docs/PYTHON_TESTING.md`\n    41→- Coverage collected only in CI (`TF_BUILD=true`)\n    42→\n    43→## Agent Architecture (Common Pattern)\n    44→\n    45→Each agent follows this pattern:\n    46→- `src/registry.ts` - Agent config: ID, model, versions, skills, flights, filters\n    47→- `src/<agent-name>.ts` - Main agent implementation\n    48→- `src/prompts/<version>/` - Prompt files, skills (`skills/<name>/SKILL.md`), sub-agents (`subagents/<name>.md`)\n    49→\n    50→Agents register skills, flight-based overrides, and filter rules in `registry.ts`. The `modules/api` module provides the internal handler registry for message routing.\n    51→\n    52→## Environment Configuration\n    53→\n    54→- Copy `.env.example` to `.env` at repo root\n    55→- All config vars use `OAGENT_` prefix (e.g., `OAGENT_AGENTID`, `OAGENT_FLIGHTS`)\n    56→- Default API URL: `http://localhost:6010`\n    57→- Agent selection: `OAGENT_AGENTID=create-agent` (default)\n    58→\n    59→## Logging Rules\n    60→\n    61→- **NEVER** include user data (filenames, content, queries) in `logInfo`, `logWarn`, `logError` -- these go to telemetry\n    62→- `logDebug` is local-only, OK for user data\n    63→- Do not use `console.*` in production code -- ESLint enforces `@officeagent/core` logging\n    64→\n    65→## CLI Tool (`oagent`)\n    66→\n    67→```powershell\n    68→oagent ping                          # Health check\n    69→oagent gen \"<prompt>\" --open         # Generate and open document\n    70→oagent gen \"<prompt>\" -f flag1 flag2 # Generate with flight flags\n    71→oagent config get                    # View configuration\n    72→oagent eval alias                    # List eval aliases\n    73→```\n    74→\n    75→## Workstream-Specific Guidance\n    76→\n    77→See agents/area-specific CLAUDE.md files:\n    78→- `agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md` - Create Agent (DOCX/PPTX/XLSX, Claude SDK)\n    79→- `agents/gpt-create-agent/CLAUDE.md` - GPT Create Agent (Azure OpenAI variant)\n    80→- `agents/ppt-creation-agent/CLAUDE.md` - PPT Creation Agent\n    81→- `agents/ppt-edit-agent/CLAUDE.md` - PPT Edit Agent\n    82→- `agents/dw-accountant-agent/CLAUDE.md` - DataWorks Accountant Agent\n    83→- `agents/dw-paralegal-agent/CLAUDE.md` - DataWorks Paralegal Agent\n    84→- `agents/odsp-agent/CLAUDE.md` - ODSP Agent\n    85→- `eval/CLAUDE.md` - Evaluation Framework\n    86→\n    87→## Best Practices\n    88→\n    89→See `docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md` for code organization, agent development patterns, testing, build/deploy, and common pitfalls.\n    90→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ca2943fe-f70a-4277-bb1d-0707b0610e59","uuid":"91f007e4-701f-42d3-a76c-5228fa718645","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\yemishin\\OfficeAgent\\CLAUDE.md","content":"# OfficeAgent Monorepo\n\nAI agent platform for Office document creation (DOCX, PPTX, XLSX, PDF), running in Docker containers with Claude SDK and Azure OpenAI harnesses.\n\n## Shell Requirements\n\n**CRITICAL: Use PowerShell for all yarn, oagent, and gulp commands.** Bash/sh will fail for build/run operations. File searching (grep, find, glob) works in any shell.\n\n## Repository Structure\n\n- `agents/` - Agent implementations (create-agent, gpt-create-agent, ppt-creation-agent, ppt-edit-agent, dw-accountant-agent, dw-paralegal-agent, odsp-agent)\n- `modules/` - Shared libraries (`@officeagent/*`): core, api, message-protocol, grounding, rai, excel-headless, chain-of-thought, html2pptx, json-to-docx-ooxml, mcp-proxy, gpt-agent, git-remote-spo\n- `.devtools/` - CLI (`oagent`), test-client, e2e-tests, eval-browser, launcher, OCV tools\n- `eval/` - Python evaluation framework (pytest-based)\n- `docs/` - Architecture documentation\n- `docker/` - Dockerfile, runtime package.json, docker-compose\n\n## Build & Run Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `npm run setup` | First-time dev environment setup |\n| `yarn build` | Build packages + Docker image (Docker Desktop must be running) |\n| `yarn start` | Start Docker container + test client |\n| `yarn start:compose` | Start via docker-compose (supports scaling) |\n| `yarn stop` | Stop Docker container |\n| `yarn reload` | Hot-reload code into running container |\n| `yarn test` | Run all tests (Jest + pytest) |\n| `yarn lint` | ESLint across all workspaces |\n\n## Package Management\n\n- **Buildtime**: Yarn 4.10.3 workspaces with `lage` task runner\n- **Runtime (in container)**: npm for Node packages (`docker/package.json`), pip/tdnf for Python (`docker/Dockerfile`)\n- Packages use `@officeagent/` scope with `workspace:^` linking\n\n## Testing\n\n- **TypeScript/JS**: Jest with ts-jest preset. Tests in `**/tests/**/*.test.ts`\n- **Python**: pytest with coverage. Tests in `tests/test_*.py`. See `docs/PYTHON_TESTING.md`\n- Coverage collected only in CI (`TF_BUILD=true`)\n\n## Agent Architecture (Common Pattern)\n\nEach agent follows this pattern:\n- `src/registry.ts` - Agent config: ID, model, versions, skills, flights, filters\n- `src/<agent-name>.ts` - Main agent implementation\n- `src/prompts/<version>/` - Prompt files, skills (`skills/<name>/SKILL.md`), sub-agents (`subagents/<name>.md`)\n\nAgents register skills, flight-based overrides, and filter rules in `registry.ts`. The `modules/api` module provides the internal handler registry for message routing.\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n- Copy `.env.example` to `.env` at repo root\n- All config vars use `OAGENT_` prefix (e.g., `OAGENT_AGENTID`, `OAGENT_FLIGHTS`)\n- Default API URL: `http://localhost:6010`\n- Agent selection: `OAGENT_AGENTID=create-agent` (default)\n\n## Logging Rules\n\n- **NEVER** include user data (filenames, content, queries) in `logInfo`, `logWarn`, `logError` -- these go to telemetry\n- `logDebug` is local-only, OK for user data\n- Do not use `console.*` in production code -- ESLint enforces `@officeagent/core` logging\n\n## CLI Tool (`oagent`)\n\n```powershell\noagent ping                          # Health check\noagent gen \"<prompt>\" --open         # Generate and open document\noagent gen \"<prompt>\" -f flag1 flag2 # Generate with flight flags\noagent config get                    # View configuration\noagent eval alias                    # List eval aliases\n```\n\n## Workstream-Specific Guidance\n\nSee agents/area-specific CLAUDE.md files:\n- `agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md` - Create Agent (DOCX/PPTX/XLSX, Claude SDK)\n- `agents/gpt-create-agent/CLAUDE.md` - GPT Create Agent (Azure OpenAI variant)\n- `agents/ppt-creation-agent/CLAUDE.md` - PPT Creation Agent\n- `agents/ppt-edit-agent/CLAUDE.md` - PPT Edit Agent\n- `agents/dw-accountant-agent/CLAUDE.md` - DataWorks Accountant Agent\n- `agents/dw-paralegal-agent/CLAUDE.md` - DataWorks Paralegal Agent\n- `agents/odsp-agent/CLAUDE.md` - ODSP Agent\n- `eval/CLAUDE.md` - Evaluation Framework\n\n## Best Practices\n\nSee `docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md` for code organization, agent development patterns, testing, build/deploy, and common pitfalls.\n","numLines":90,"startLine":1,"totalLines":90}}}
